Global Magnetic Materials for New Energy Vehicle Market Insights
Magnetic Materials for New Energy Vehicle Market size was valued at USD 10.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 20.4 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.8% from 2024 to 2030.

Magnetic Materials for New Energy Vehicle Market Overview
The magnetic materials for the new energy vehicle (NEV) market is projected to witness significant growth, driven by the increasing demand for electric vehicles (EVs) and advancements in automotive technologies. In 2023, the global market value for magnetic materials in NEVs reached approximately USD 12.3 billion, with forecasts indicating a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 16.2% from 2024 to 2030. This growth is fueled by the rising adoption of electric and hybrid vehicles, which heavily rely on magnetic materials for components such as motors, batteries, and powertrains. The growing emphasis on energy efficiency and sustainability further supports the demand for high-performance magnetic materials in the automotive sector.

